commit.message:
scripted-diff: force set python source file encoding to utf-8

-BEGIN VERIFY SCRIPT-
sed -i 's/#!\/usr\/bin\/env python3/#!\/usr\/bin\/env python3\n# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-/g' $(git ls-files -- '*.py')
-END VERIFY SCRIPT-

commit.message: lint: use utf-8 to read python source file

verification.payload:
tree fb874c5b665c4511359473c7c2c91b0a19060fe6
parent 52623b7bff1adc6568dddf6f34fc0809ffcc6a0e
author Chun Kuan Lee <ken2812221@gmail.com> 1537324586 +0800
committer Chun Kuan Lee <ken2812221@gmail.com> 1537324899 +0000

lint: use utf-8 to read python source file

files.patch:
@@ -5,8 +5,8 @@ export LC_ALL=C
 EXIT_CODE=0
 for PYTHON_FILE in $(git ls-files -- "*.py"); do
     if [[ $(head -c 2 "${PYTHON_FILE}") == "#!" &&
-          $(head -n 1 "${PYTHON_FILE}") != "#!/usr/bin/env python3" ]]; then
-        echo "Missing shebang \"#!/usr/bin/env python3\" in ${PYTHON_FILE} (do not use python or python2)"
+          $(head -n 2 "${PYTHON_FILE}") != "#!/usr/bin/env python3"$'\n'"# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-" ]]; then
+        echo "Missing shebang \"#!/usr/bin/env python3\" or \"# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\" in ${PYTHON_FILE} (do not use python or python2)"
         EXIT_CODE=1
     fi
 done
